article.headline: CS Bakersfield 59, CS Northridge 57
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Trent Blakley scored 16 points and hit a running jumper at the buzzer to give Cal State Bakersfield a 59-57 victory over Cal State Northridge on Wednesday night. Stephon Carter added 14 points for the Roadrunners (6-17), who led by as many as 12 in the second half but saw their advantage evaporate in the closing minutes. Kenny Daniels led the Matadors (9-15) with 24 points. Northridge's Lenny Daniel tied the score at 57 on a jumper with 20 seconds to play after Santwon Latunde put Bakersfield up by two with a pair of free throws. Blakley then hit the game-winning shot from the top of the key. Bakersfield led 54-46 with 4:32 remaining before Northridge put together a 9-1 run to tie the score at 55. A dunk by Willie Galick and three-point play by Daniels capped the run.
